#: help_to_heat/templates/frontdoor/wall-type.html:37
msgid ""
"Solid brick walls will have an alternating pattern, with some bricks laid "
"across the wall so you can see the smaller ends from the outside."
msgstr ""
"Bydd gan waliau brics solet batrwm bob yn ail, gyda rhai brics wedi'u gosod "
"ar draws y wal fel y gallwch weld y pennau llai o'r tu allan."

#: help_to_heat/templates/frontdoor/wall-type.html:41
msgid ""
"If your home has cavity walls, the bricks typically have an even pattern "
"with all bricks laid lengthways."
msgstr ""
"Os oes gan eich aelwyd waliau ceudod, fel arfer mae gan y brics batrwm cyson "
"gyda'r holl frics wedi'u gosod ar eu hyd."

#: help_to_heat/templates/frontdoor/wall-type.html:45
msgid ""
"If the brickwork has been covered, you may be able to tell by measuring the "
"width of the wall. Measure the depth of the wall by a window or door on one "
"of your external walls."
msgstr ""
"Os yw'r gwaith brics wedi'i orchuddio, efallai y byddwch yn gallu dweud trwy "
"fesur lled y wal. Mesurwch ddyfnder y wal wrth ffenestr neu ddrws ar un o'ch "
"waliau allanol."

#: help_to_heat/templates/frontdoor/wall-type.html:49
msgid ""
"If a brick wall is more than 260mm thick, then it is probably a cavity wall."
msgstr ""
"Os yw wal frics yn fwy na 260mm o drwch, yna mae'n debyg mai wal ceudod yw "
"hi."

#: help_to_heat/templates/frontdoor/wall-type.html:53
msgid ""
"A narrower wall is probably a solid wall. Stone walls may be thicker still "
"but are usually solid."
msgstr ""
"Mae'n debygol bod wal gulach yn wal solet. Gall waliau cerrig fod yn fwy "
"trwchus o hyd ond fel arfer maen nhw'n solet."

